quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  46,21,"And mention the brother of ?Ad, when he warned his people by the sand dunes; warners had passed away before him and after him, [saying], “Worship none but God. Truly I fear for you the punishment of a tremendous day.”"
  46,22,"They said, “Have you come to us to pervert us from our gods? Then bring upon us that wherewith you have threatened us, if you are among the truthful.”"
  46,23,"He said, “Knowledge lies with God alone, and I only convey to you that wherewith I have been sent. But I see that you are an ignorant people.”"
  46,24,"And when they beheld it as a cloud bound for their valleys, they said, “This is a cloud bringing us rain.” Nay! It is what you sought to hasten—a wind carrying a painful punishment"
  46,25,destroying everything by the Command of its Lord. They became such that naught was seen but their dwellings. Thus do We recompense the guilty people
  46,26,"Indeed We established them in a manner in which We did not establish you, and We endowed them with hearing, sight, and hearts. But their hearing, sight, and hearts availed them naught, since they rejected God’s signs, and that which they used to mock beset them"
  46,27,"And indeed We destroyed the towns around you, and We vary the signs that haply they might return"
  46,28,"Why, then, did they—whom they had taken as gods apart from God and as a means of drawing nigh [unto God]—not help them? Nay, they forsook them. That was their perversion and that which they used to fabricate"
  46,29,"And [remember] when We made a group of jinn incline unto thee, listening to the Quran, when in its presence they said, “Hearken!” Then when it came to an end, they went back to their people as warners"
  46,30,"They said, “O our people! Truly we have heard a Book sent down after Moses, confirming that which came before it, guiding to the truth and to a straight road"
  46,31,"O our people! Answer God’s caller and believe in him, then He will forgive you some of your sins and protect you from a painful punishment"
  46,32,And whosoever does not answer God’s caller thwarts not on earth and has no protectors apart from Him—they are in manifest error.”
  46,33,"Have they not considered that God, Who created the heavens and the earth and did not weary in their creation, is able to give life to the dead? Yea! He is Powerful over all things"
  46,34,"On the day when those who disbelieve are exposed to the Fire: “Is this not true?” They will say, “Yea, by our Lord!” He will reply, “Taste the punishment for having disbelieved.”"
  46,35,"So be patient, as the resolute among the messengers were patient. And seek not to hasten for them. It shall be for them, on the day when they see that which they are promised, as though they had tarried naught but an hour of a day. A proclamation! Will any but the iniquitous people be destroyed"
  47,1,Those who disbelieve and turn from the way of God—He has made their deeds go astray
  47,2,"And those who believe and perform righteous deeds, and believe in what has been sent down unto Muhammad—and it is the truth from their Lord—He has absolved them of their evil deeds and set their state aright"
  47,3,That is because those who disbelieve follow falsehood and because those who believe follow the truth from their Lord. Thus does God set forth for mankind their likenesses
  47,4,"When you meet those who disbelieve, strike at their necks; then, when you have overwhelmed them, tighten the bonds. Then free them graciously or hold them for ransom, till war lays down its burdens. Thus [shall it be]. And if God willed, He would take vengeance upon them, but that He may test some of you by means of others, And as for those who are slain in the way of God, He will not make their deeds go astray"
  47,5,He will guide them and set their state aright
  47,6,"and cause them to enter the Garden, having made it known to them"
  47,7,"you who believe! If you help God, He will help you and make firm your steps"
  47,8,"As for those who disbelieve, wretched are they, and He has made their deeds go astray"
  47,9,"That is because they were averse to that which God sent down, so He made their deeds come to naught"